        <descriptionSet>
            <description>The trial of Lynette “Squeaky” Fromme for attempting to assassinate United States President Gerald Ford began on November 4, 1975.  Three days before the trial began, President Ford gave a videotape testimony from the White House as a defense witness in the trial of Fromme.  The testimony was the first time a President testified at a criminal trial. Throughout the trial Fromme was disruptive and often had to watch the proceedings via close-circuit television because of her outbursts.</description>
